parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities that could have been mitigated or prevented.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without a crash or impact
causing injuries
such as abrasions
chemical skin burns
or other harm to vehicle occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the horn can lead to a lack of audible warning in emergency situations, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The horn fails to work
usually when the vehicle is parked
the horn is unresponsive
the horn only works occasionally.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ability of the key to come out of the ignition when the car is not in park can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The key can come out of the ignition when the car is not in park
the key is loose in the ignition
the vehicle can roll or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the flywheel can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
difficulty starting the vehicle in cold weather
the vehicle may have trouble maintaining speed or power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the thermostat can cause the engine to overheat or run at suboptimal temperatures, leading to reduced engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing damage to the engine.
symptoms: The heater blows cold air
the engine overheats
the engine runs rough or misfires
the vehicle may have trouble maintaining speed or power.
